Peru Stocks: Aceros Arequipa, Relapasa, Southern Copper, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-09-09T20:47:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-09/peru-stocks-aceros-arequipa-relapasa-southern-copper-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index fell 0.9 percent to 19,906.55. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index dropped 1.4 percent to 2,640.34.  Industrial shares fell after U.S. stocks dropped, said
Hernando Pastor, an analyst at Lima-based Juan Magot y Asociados
SAB.  Cementos Lima SAA (CEMLIMI1 PE), the country’s biggest
cement maker, declined 2.7 percent to 2.20 soles. Corp. Aceros
Arequipa SA (CORAREI1 PE), the Lima-based steelmaker, fell 2.1
percent to 2.36 soles.  Casa Grande  (CASAGRC1 PE), Peru’s largest
sugar producer and a unit of Gloria SA, slid 1.4 percent to
14.10 soles after futures dropped in New York. Refineria la
Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s Repsol YPF SA known
as Relapasa, dropped 1.2 percent to 81 centimos after crude fell
in New York.  Copper and zinc miners declined after metals slumped in New
York and London,  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, fell 7.1 percent to 13 cents.  Southern
Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , Peru’s biggest copper producer, dropped
3.9 percent to $30.75.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian
copper and gold exploration company, declined 2.3 percent to 42
cents. Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
producer, fell 1.7 percent to 2.86 soles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
